      "blocks": {
        "fi-eyebrow": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>About the studio</p>",
            "size": "sm",
            "uppercase": true,
            "muted": true
          }
        },
        "fi-heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Founded on the idea that a wedding should feel like the people in it.",
            "size": "4xl"
          }
        },
        "fi-text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Everafter was started by Clara Marche in 2016, after a friend's wedding pulled her into planning work she hadn't expected to love. A decade later, the studio is still small on purpose — four people, eight to ten weddings a year, every engagement led by a named planner from first call to final goodbye.</p><p>We don't have a house style, exactly. We have a set of beliefs: that the best weddings are specific to the couple, that candlelight beats stage lighting, that a long dinner is worth a short ceremony, and that the people running the day should love the couple almost as much as the couple loves each other.</p>",
            "size": "base"
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["fi-eyebrow", "fi-heading", "fi-text"]
    },
